Thierry Schellenbach has implemented a Prototype plugin that allows you to do cross site remoting using the dynamic script tag method that other frameworks such as Dojo and jQuery have supported for awhile. You can implement this by simply setting crossSite: true as a config parameter to Ajax.Request: PLAIN TEXT JAVASCRIPT:
&#160;
new Ajax.Request&#40;'myurl', &#123;
&#160; method: 'GET',
&#160; crossSite: true,
&#160; parameters: [...]

	Julien Lecomte has written up the pattern where you use setTimeout() to keep yielding control back to the main thread so that it can handle browser events.
